race.comment: HOLD THIS (3) justified the good support on debut ($1.90 fav), when a narrow second over 1175m in the small field at this track. Further improved now and finds a fairly ordinary contest. Goes close. LIL ORLOV (7) kept safe in betting on debut when struggled in the heavy (9) going for a tiring sixth over 1200m at Ballarat. Will relish the claim and capable of better on the firmer surface. ALL CHIPS IN (2) Four-year-old Dundeel gelding from Group 1 winning mare Sunday Joy, on debut for the Craig Widdison yard. Wasn't asked to do much in the two latest jump outs and must be kept safe. AEROFOIL (1) deep into the preparation when improving sharply to finish second over 1200m at Tumut. Drawn out and place claims look best.
